column5: Anyone know some sites where one could download lake topo maps from the net?  Some creative google search (utilizing google search parameters) can give some results but...  I am looking for some ftp site or something.  If you know any, please PM me.   Thank you.      Looking for a lake? PM me, I may just happen to have it.
Not sure if this is what your after, but have a look.......  http://atlas.nrcan.gc.ca/site/english/maps/topo/map  Sinker
If you go to www.anglersatlas.com and register, they give you some lakes for free.
Pm'd you links to charts I scanned last year, Kawarthas-Georgian Bay and Bay of Quinte. Feel free to forward links to anyone that needs them, mods didn't want the links posted for copyright reasons.
